Etiology of community acquired pneumonia in inpatients children. Uruguay 1998-2004. Community acquired bacterial pneumonia represents 8.7% of overall discharges of children under 15 years old in the Pediatric Hospital of the Centro Hospitalario Pereira Rossell since 1997 treatment guidelines are being applied. Changes in etiology of this disease in children hospitalized in our institution from 1998 to 2004 were studied. Streptococcus pneumoniae was the most frequent agent in every year of the period, 91.4 +/- 2.3%